  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "VESSEL SUPPLY – LAST MILE DELIVERY ASSISTANT",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>FREIGHT FORWARDING, PACKING AND CRATING SERVICES VALUE ADDED LOGISTICS PROVIDERS FREIGHT TRANSPORT ARRANGEMENT</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will support the logistics team by picking, packing, and preparing goods for delivery while ensuring accurate cargo handling and assisting drivers to deliver safely and on time to vessels.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Pick and pack goods accurately to prepare orders for delivery</li><li>Check and count cargo during port deliveries to ensure accuracy and condition</li><li>Handle cargo carefully to maintain safety and prevent damage during loading and unloading</li><li>Assist Class 4 drivers by coordinating and supporting timely and safe delivery to vessels</li><li>Scan, record, and recover returned items to maintain accurate inventory records</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Valid forklift licence</li><li>Experience delivering cargo to port (PT / MSW / PSA)</li><li>Rigger & Signalman course certificate</li><li>Completed PSA Safety Course</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Salary: S$2,600 – S$3,200 per month (Includes allowances and overtime pay)</li><li>Work Location: Pandan Loop, Singapore</li></ul><p>Work Schedule:</p><ul><li>6 working days per week (4 rest days per month)</li><li>Day Shift: 8.30 AM – 5.30 PM</li><li>Night Shift: 11.00 PM – 8.00 AM</li><li>Overtime applies after standard working hours</li></ul><p>Important Notice to Applicants Maritime delivery work is time-sensitive, and delays may cause serious operational impact. To ensure safety, punctuality and sufficient rest:</p><ul><li>All employees must reside in Singapore</li><li>Daily commuting from Johor Bahru (JB) is strictly not allowed</li></ul><p>How to Apply</p><ul><li>WhatsApp Ms Catherine: 9244 0070</li></ul>",
